    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-31T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-31T00:00:00-05:00" n="584"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d584">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.516/32.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to <gloss
                            type="to">Vice President Wehrhane of the National Bank of
                        Haiti</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-31">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 31, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Department has received cable from Port au Prince with request to forward to you,
                    which it does, paraphrased, as follows: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>The Haitian Government took from our vaults $65,000. It claims this
                            action to be in the execution of the judgment following the law of
                            August 14th.</p>
                        <p rend="right">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Williams</hi>.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
